Package io.frictionlessdata.tableschema.field

Class Field<T>

java.lang.Object
io.frictionlessdata.tableschema.field.Field<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
AnyField, ArrayField, BooleanField, DateField, DatetimeField, DurationField, GeojsonField, GeopointField, IntegerField, NumberField, ObjectField, StringField, TimeField, YearField, YearmonthField
public abstract class Field<T> extends Object
Definition of a field in a data table. Doesn't hold values Spec: http://frictionlessdata.io/specs/table-schema/index.html#field-descriptors

      public abstract T parseValue(String value, String format, Map<String,Object> options) throws TypeInferringException
      Parse string value into Java object according to the Field type. If `value` can't be parsed, throw a TypeInferringException
      Parameters:
      value - String serialization of Field value
      format - applicable format
      options - applicable options
      Returns:
      Deserialized object
      Throws:
      TypeInferringException - if parsing fails because value can't be parsed

    • parseFormat

      public abstract String parseFormat(String value, Map<String,Object> options)
      Given a value, try to parse the format. Some Field types don't have variant formats and will always return `default`
      Parameters:
      value - sample value encoded as string
      options - format options
      Returns:
      inferred format encoded as a string

    • castValue

      public T castValue(String value) throws InvalidCastException, ConstraintsException
      Use the Field definition to cast a value into the Field type. Enforces constraints by default.
      Parameters:
      value - the value string to cast
      Returns:
      result of the cast operation
      Throws:
      InvalidCastException - if the content of `value` cannot be cast to the destination type
      ConstraintsException - thrown if `enforceConstraints` was set to `true`and constraints were violated

      Returns:

    • similar

      public boolean similar(Field<?> other)
      Similar to equals(Object), but disregards the `format` property to allow for Schemas that are similar except that Fields have no defined format. Also treats null and empty string the same for `name` and `type`.
      Parameters:
      other - the Field to compare against
      Returns:
      true if the other Field is equals ignoring the format, false otherwise

    • equals

      public boolean equals(Object o)
      Disregards optional properties like `title`. Regards two fields as equal if they are either the same or of the same type, have the same name and the same format and constraints.
      Overrides:
      equals in class Object
      Parameters:
      o - Another Field to check for equality
      Returns:
      true if both Fields are equal
